(82, 1, '2018-01-24 06:34:01', '2018-01-24 06:34:01', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image=\"115\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Water Analysis\"][vc_column_text]Our staff performs water testing for inorganic and volatile organic compounds for drinking, domestic and waste water. We have instrumentation dedicated to water testing and test for all the regulated and non-regulated compounds of concern. Our Labs carry out a wider range of analyses relevant to the health related parameters laid down by WHO water quality standards.\r\n\r\nWe provide information on techniques of water sampling and carry out various analysis on water. Parameters covered in our analysis include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alkalinity</li>\r\n	<li>pH</li>\r\n	<li>Dissolved Oxygen (DO)</li>\r\n	<li>Biological Oxygen Demand (BOD)</li>\r\n	<li>Chemical Oxygen Demand (COD)</li>\r\n	<li>Bromate (BrO3-)</li>\r\n	<li>Electrical Conductivity</li>\r\n	<li>Nitrates</li>\r\n	<li>Nitrogen Kjedahl</li>\r\n	<li>Phosphates</li>\r\n	<li>Sulphates</li>\r\n	<li>Turbidity</li>\r\n	<li>Essential trace elements like Magnesium, Zinc, Iron etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Heavy metals like lead, mercury, arsenic, cadmium etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Water Analysis', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'water-analysis', '', '', '2018-01-24 07:05:47', '2018-01-24 07:05:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost/csi-new/?page_id=82', 0, 'page', '', 0),
